item.title: Command Help!
item.dc:creator: @ILOVEJAVA ILOVEJAVA
item.description:
@ILOVEJAVA wrote:

if you don’t have a client.java, you need to add it to io\packets\commands and find a different teleport command to see what it should look like. that’s only for bulby or mezzy. also, where you have “if (cmd[0].equals(”::home"))" it should be “if (cmd[0].equals(“home”))” because the extra :: means you would have to type ::::home. and i think your p.teleporttoX and p.teleporttoY are wrong. the coords should be set up differently. (once again, if you have mezzy or bulby source). if you need further help, just ask. i know that i didn’t explain very well…so sorry…lol

item.title: Command Help!
item.dc:creator: @sheercoldpvp sheercoldpvp
item.description:
@sheercoldpvp wrote:

go to client.java

click the buttons ctrl+f on your keyboard.

a search window will appear.

search for command

look for others similar to yours

then after the last } in the command

click enter on your keyboard

and put your code after it then exit, save, and compile it

hope this helps!
